inn1.comm: Wood steams in a hits a good length outside off, Cross pushes forward... and there's a click as the ball goes through! But no one appeals, and there was a gap between bat and ball. Must have been a spike in the pitch
slightly short, 85mph at the body, Cross tucks it down towards square and they hustle through
slightly short of a length, nibbling on off stump, Coetzer jumps across and blocks
zips through, beaten playing off the back foot, 85mph and seaming a fraction past the bat and into the gloves
goes fuller, 87mph around middle and off, punched back to the bowler
tight stuff to start with, on a length and Coetzer can only get forward to tap defensively down the pitch
slightly leg side and swerving behind Cross
back of a length, 79mph and this is basically a long hop that allows Cross to free the arms and flay the first boundary of the day through point
finds his length, this swings in a touch as Cross defends
Willey bowling over the wicket, angled across and steered down to third man with an open face
full, 83mph and swinging in a touch as Coetzer steps on to the front foot and spanks a drive to extra cover
touch short, around off stump and punched watchfully back down the track
back of a length and this comes in a fraction, clips the inside edge and runs behind square leg
dug in short, head-hunting bumper but Coetzer takes it on, slightly ungainly hoick off the splice but it clears the leg-side field and gambols away for a couple
shortish, nipping back in to hit the inside edge as Coezter pushes in front of his body, deflected on to the thigh
beautiful shot! Not overly full from Wood, but Coetzer opens up his body and crumps an emphatic drive through the covers for four
length ball, presses out and pushes to cover
pitched up, 86mph and shovelled off the front pad... just clears Willey's dive at mid-on! Struck it pretty well, but his heart might just have popped up to tickle his tonsils for a moment
timed down the ground, a couple more here... Coetzer hanging back and forcing the ball past mid-on, just a checked punch
pitched up, holding its line on off, blocked
pushed across, gentle pace and Cross is out of his crease, stroked confidently through cover point for four
length, chopped down square on the off side
touch of inswing, 81mph and Cross blocks, Willey trots across to field in his follow through
better lines from Willey, again this is defended back to the bowler
sweet as a nut, sweet like Tropicana! Lovely batting from Cross, good balance and he's up on his toes to slam a back-foot punch through the covers for his third boundary
shortish, good licks and Coetzer jumps across to defend
bit of width, frees the arms and slices one down to third man
fullish, 86mph outside off, prodded to cover
pitched up in the channel, Cross comes across but doesn't time the drive

hammers in the bouncer, Cross swings for the hills and gets a b-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-g top edge over backward square leg... but there's no man out there for it, Hales has to sprint back from square leg and they get a couple more
length on the pads, sliding in and worked across the line
pitched up and tapped square from the crease
launched! Hit off a length, on the up and timed superbly, clears mid-off and goes scudding away for four more
pushed across the bows and steered towards point
full length, 81mph and Coetzer again brings out his tally whacker, picks out cover this time
dug in short of a length, stabbed towards cover on the back foot
pitched up, 80mph and pinged back on the drive, Willey gets a hand on it and the ball squirms past the stumps with Cross diving to regain his ground
good length, 86mph on off stump, Cross presses out to defend
shortish and tapped down into the off side
back of a length, rising up nicely off this crisp deck for Cross to throw the hands and lash four wide of third man
tighter line, 86mph and punched into the covers coming across
good length, aiming for the top of off stump, blocked towards mid-off
fuller, this time Cross drives without timing, mid-off prevents the single
slower ball from Willey, but Coetzer seems to pick it and heaves up and over midwicket, bounces away to the rope
pitched up and slapped to cover
back of a length, 79mph and clipped away through square leg
taking the pace off again but Cross is equal to it and deftly glides the ball between short third man and backward point for four
banged in short but this is leg side and all he has to do its help it away, spanked hard over the man on the edge of the ring for another boundary to fine leg - Scotland raise 50 in the eighth over
drilled through the covers, beautiful shot-making! Three in a row for Cross, who's motoring at well above a run a ball
this skids through over leg stump, slippery length from Wood and Coetzer swings and misses
lovely stuff, this time Coetzer pings four through the covers off the back foot, superb timing once again
pitched up, another swing and a miss
fullish length, 88mph and speared towards cover
pitched up, Coetzer clears the front foot and belts it over mid-on, Wood yelps in frustration as it skips away for four more
digs in the bouncer, flying through... Lucky not to get called a wide on height, that

slides a googly on, into the front pad... looked leg side but England review Marais Erasmus' not-out decision. Nope, that was definitely sliding down, not even clipping according to Hawk-Eye so England lose that one
pushes through the wrong'un again, Cross tries to cut off the back foot and nearly gets into trouble
tossed up on middle and leg, gets the sweep away, nicely played and it scoots for four
flat delivery on the stumps, worked for one through midwicket
out the front of the hand, I think, touch short but skidding on and Coetzer jabs it back to the bowler
floated up and turned into the leg side for one
pitched up, cross seam outside off, Coetzer has a big swing and misses
comes across and pokes into the covers
length, in the channel and Coetzer spanks one to the cover sweeper
angled in and flipped away through square leg for one
shortish in the corridor and Coetzer slaps a big top edge over backward point... but it bounces well in front of Hales running around the rope and then evades his diving effort to go for four
length, 81mph and defended on off stump
punched off the back foot for one down the ground
flighted, Coetzer looks to have been done here and completely miscues a lofted drive off the inside half of the bat, bounces well short of mid-on though
tossed up and hoicked over the leg side, just a single
pushed through and dabbed off the back foot through point, Willey slides to cut it off on the boundary
floated up on off and pushed square
straighter line and Coetzer gets down to sweep a single
length delivery, 82mph outside off, Coetzer draws himself up and caresses the ball between mid-off and extra cover... classy stuff, that's four more
comes across and prods this to cover

room to free the arms, Coetzer hammers it out of the ground! Superbly well struck, over the tents at wide long-off - that's another powerful statement of intent and brings Scotland's captain his fifty!
squirted into the leg side
lovely shot, this is rifled through the covers, Plunkett getting the treatment now
in the channel, swing and a miss to finish the over
floated up, again Coetzer latches on to it... and deposits six down the ground at long-off He's having fun out there, bringing up Scotland's 100 with another sweet strike
flatter, Coetzer defends into the ground by his toes
presses forward to defend on the off stump

gottim, Rashid breaks through! Think that is caught behind, as Coetzer presses forward to get an inside edge on to his front pad, Billings snaffling it up - and there's no review as Erasmus raises his finger. Superb knock from the captain, though
pushed through and defended
tosses up the legbreak, goes back and across to defend
length outside off, Cross watches it through
short and wide, cross seam but skidding on nicely for Cross to sit back and larrup four through point, behind the sweeper in the deep
better line, Cross comes across
length, 81mph on off, defended into the covers
top of off, 82mph from Plunkett, who's looked a bit creaky so far, Cross blocks

Plunkett gets him, nicked to the keeper! Some relief from England, silencing both openers after an impressive salvo... Cross misses out on fifty, he was just trying to glide that to third man, I think, but ended up steering a simple catch to Billings
flat legbreak, MacLeod drops back and swats one in front of midwicket
tossed up and prodded into the covers
flighted, leg side but straightening and Berrington pops it towards midwicket
on the stumps and tapped away
tight lines from Rashid, defended on the front foot
legbreak pushed through outside off, Berrington goes back and stabs towards cover point - just one off the over
slightly short outside off, dabbed down towards Roy at backward point
slashed, in the air but wide of third man, Tom Curran is on as a sub fielder and he does good work to prevent a boundary sliding across to his right
length, poked into a gap for one
Berrington comes across on off stump and blocks
pitched up, 81mph and he goes for the drive, mistimed into the covers
stays back in the crease and nudges a shortish delivery off his pads to get off the mark
plays back and pushes to the bowler
hint of spin outside off, left alone
uses his feet, doesn't quite get to the pitch but is able to push into the covers
brings out the sweep, takes it from around off stump behind square on the leg side
dropped at slip! Full outside off, he goes for the drive, it's a low chance to Root's left and he can't hang on. Was another googly
takes a thick inside edge into the leg side
this one goes straight on outside off, MacLeod playing back and it takes a thick outside edge into backward point
presses forward into a good length delivery, plays to cover
strong sweep from outside off, a tumbling save from Bairstow at deep square
attempts another sweep, doesn't make contact, there's a muted appeal from Moeen it's well outside the line of off stump
deep in the crease to a shorter delivery and pushed down the ground
touch short, he rocks back and pulls to deep midwicket
big shot! A solid swing through the line as Rashid gives it a touch of air and sends it over long-on
full outside off, strides forward and defends to cover
a straighter one, flatter, defended to cover
goes for the sweep, takes a top edge into his chest
another googly, straight, defended to the off side
full at the stumps, blocked back to the bowler
swept to deep square leg
tries to guide this down to third man and almost provides an edge to Billings as it beats the top edge
hint of a leading edge here as tries to work to the leg side
a shorter delivery, bunted down to long-on with a straight bat
down the pitch, gets to this almost on the full and it's driven off the toe end towards mid-off
short of a length outside off, driven to deep cover
low full toss, he takes advantage with a powerful sweep which skims along the ground in front of square
and another sweep, there's a superb piece of fielding by Plunkett at deeps square to prevent another boundary
an appeal for lbw as a googly spins past the inside edge and takes the front pad...England have no reviews left. Was going over the stumps
places this nicely behind point with a cut as Rashid drops a little short
there's a leg-break, tapped square into the off side
another wrong 'un, takes the inside edge as Berrington plays forward and it scuttles behind square on the leg side
can't get this past midwicket with a flick off the back foot
comes down the track, isn't quite to the pitch and it takes an outside edge to short third man
nicely bowled, full outside off, holds its line and pushed to the covers
tries to sweep this from well outside off, gets taken on the back leg
opens the face and dabbed towards short third man...a good call from MacLeod for the single
plays back and nudges square into the off side with an open face
over the wicket, short of a length at leg stump, goes for a pull and it loops towards square leg off the hip
short of a length outside off, angled down to third man
keeps it back of a length, dropped down into the off side for a quick single
touch fuller, on leg stump, pushed into the leg side
good length at off stump, opens the face down to third man
gets forward into a good length delivery and defends to cover
they've swept well so far, this is another, fetched from outside off and splits the deep field on the leg side
this time it's a sweep behind square, lovely placement, toying with the field...Bairstow dives but can't cut it off
is that three in a row? Not quite, super work on the boundary by Willey, as MacLeod nails another sweep through square leg
touch short outside off, square drives to deep cover
this spins a touch from outside off, takes an inside edge into the pad
driven to deep cover
full outside off, driven to backward point
down the pitch and nearly finds mid-off as he drives, but it's just short of Plunkett who then does well to stop it
full outside off, driven to deep cover
top shot! Beautifully driven straight down the ground, a late flick of the bottom hand to aid the placement
banged in short of a length, dabbed fine of backward point
good length delivery at the stumps, pushed towards point
down the pitch then flicks to midwicket
shorter outside off, he steps back outside leg stump and places this wide of deep cover
worked down the ground to long-on
tucked off the pads into midwicket
super uses of the feet and then he pumps it straight down the ground, just short of being another six
gets forward and pushes into the off side
short of a length, straight, played off the back foot to point
touch of width outside off, short of a length, not much timing in this cut shot
crunched through the off side! Touch of width, gentle pace, MacLeod gets onto the front foot and it's flayed through the covers
straightens his line and almost dragged as it takes the inside part of the bat and bounces close to leg stump
on the pads, flicked to deep square leg
on leg stump, deflects off the thigh pad
pushed into the covers
excellent placement, uses his feet and then flicks in the air out to deep midwicket
pushed back to Moeen as he looks to work to long-on
almost out of the ground with another sweep and that brings up his half-century off 36 balls
shorter and flatter outside off, worked down the ground
tucked off the pads to deep square leg
full outside off, driven to cover
he's adjusted well to some extra bounce outside off, gets underneath it and sends it down to third man 200 up
good length, pushed to cover
short of a length outside off, played into backward point
good catch from Root as he runs back from mid-off...Berrington looking to go down the ground, it's just short of a good length and a cross-seam delivery, gets too far underneath it
short of a length at off stump, gets on his toes and defends
round the wicket to the left hander, full and straight, defended
bat and pad together, runs to the leg side
no messing around! He's had a couple of sighters then brings out the reverse sweep, sent in the air behind square on the off side
good length at off stump, pushed to the covers
angled in from round the wicket, defended to the off side
cut into the off side so he'll keep the strike
a short ball outside off which climbs through to Billings at head height as Munsey drops his hands
fuller, angled across outside off, beats the outside edge as he goes for a square drive
short outside off, cut to deep point
that's a top shot! Short of a length outside off, he jumps and gets over the top, square driving behind point. Very elegant
short of a length, pushed to backward point
keeps it short outside off, angled down to third man
worked off the back foot down to long-on
a straight delivery, pushed back to the bowler
fuller, at the stumps, driven to Moeen
he nails another reverse sweep! Sends it in the air over short third man, not far from carrying for six
angled into the pads, nudged to midwicket
taken from outside off, worked with bottom hand into the leg side
short and wide, chases it with an attempted upper cut but gets the wide call
good length at off stump, pushed to the covers
brings the bottom hand into play again to shovel this towards mid-on
round the wicket, a slower ball full toss outside off, takes the bottom of the bat to mid-off
this time he crunches it! Drives on the up at a back-of-a-length delivery outside off and clears mid-off
full, straight, another slower ball, pushed to mid-off
banged in short, angled in at the body, he hooks down to long leg
dabbed away from outside off into the point area
that sweep comes out of the middle but straight to the man at deep square
good length, straight, pushed with a straight bat
tries to give himself a touch of room to the leg side but can't find a gap into the covers
this one straightens a touch and it's pushed to the covers
more air on this one, drifts into the pads, clipped to midwicket...a quiet over
short, wide, a real loosener and MacLeod is leaping to cut through backward point... the bounce nearly leaves Roy missing some teeth and it the flies to the rope for four
full, driven back down the track, Wood gets a hand on it but can only divert past the stumps with Munsey reaching for his ground
length ball, 85mph outside off, clubbed hard to the cover sweeper
short but leg side, Munsey only needs to get some glove on it to send the ball racing fine for another boundary
length, 87mph and tucking him up on leg stump, prodded back to the bowler
angled across the left-hander, who chops down behind square and they amble the one
Moeen tosses the ball up straight, Munsey defends
angled in from around the wicket, tickled down the ground
over the wicket, pushed through on off stump and MacLeod sweeps hard for one to deep square leg
here comes the reversey-Percy again, down low and swiping four up and over short third man! He's got that shot nailed
pushed through straighter, tucked to leg
floated up and Munsey works one off his legs square
short ball from Wood, clothed on the pull out to deep square
pitched up, sliding leg side as he swings across the line and gets an inside edge on to pad, they scamper back as the ball rolls behind square
length ball, worked to midwicket
Wood takes the pace off, Munsey defends to the off side
another slower ball, stabbed through the covers
on the pads, MacLeod scoops it away over square, lands a few yards short of the boundary rider - and that's the 250 up for Scotland, they are rolling on nicely
shortish and prodded through the off side
cutting his fingers over the ball, sits up for the heave to cow corner and Munsey slots it for four more!
on the stumps, swung away for a single to deeps square leg
full and straight and flipped behind square on the leg side
length ball, 80mph and Munsey dabs it down
short and slightly wide, cut firmly through point to the sweeper for one
short from Wood, but that's climbed too high for the batsman to get anything on
bumper, this is around the eyeline but Munsey plays it well, pulled flat to deep square leg
dug in as MacLeod advances, steers it down to third man
goes for the yorker, 86mph up towards the blockhole, Munsey jams down and squeezes it towards cover
touch short and angled across the southpaw Munsey, who slices one to third man
back of a length on off, 85mph and MacLeod blocks towards backward point
and there's the boundary from the extra ball to cap the over for Scotland, sliding in on to the pads, flipped neatly over backward square and away... Wood's figures spoiled further
full on the pads, Munsey gets a touch on it and Billings can't collect cleanly...
short and down the leg side
bumper, but it doesn't get up and Munsey latches on to hammer six over deep square leg, right back into the crowd!
angled across, this one isn't quite there for the pull and he fails to connect
dug in and paddled around the corner
fired full but down the leg side - another extra to the column
good ball, short and angling in at MacLeod, he ends up wearing it on the glove
length, not a bad delivery but it sits up and MacLeod had backed away, opens up and slashes four more through gully
pushed through on off, Munsey defends... and MacLeod calls him through as Billings scampers after it into the covers, needed a better throw to Rashid to bring about a run-out chance, though!
dragged down a touch, clubbed flat towards long-on
slider from Rashid, Munsey heaves across the line and gets a big top edge... but it clears the keeper and lands fine of short third man
beautifully struck through midwicket, tossed up and he waits for it, leans on a push into a gap and it races away!
slightly short, MacLeod rocks back and collars a slog-cum-pull, that's gone all the way over deep midwicket! Into the 90s with a brutal blow
fired down quick outside off, MacLeod dabs one to keep the strike
full and wide from round the wicket, MacLeod comes forward and swats one through the infield
over the wicket, full outside off, 79mph and Munsey mistimes it down towards mid-on
pitched up towards the tramlines again, jammed through backward point, MacLeod moves one closer to his milestone
pitched up and slashed through the covers coming forwards, just one to the boundary rider
pitched up very wide and MacLeod has come down early, drives but is beaten
gets the wide yorker in again and MacLeod can only tamp down on a single into the covers... But that's 300 for Scotland, as well as the 100 stand between these two. Marvelous stuff
floated up full, MacLeod again picks up a single on the sweep
worked away off the stumps, into a gap leg side and they come racing back, it's a stretch but they get two and Munsey has his maiden ODI half-century! Well played, young fella
and now the reverse-sweep aagin, clears the leaping fielder at short third man, that's four!
pushed through, the sweep it top-edged - well taken running towards short fine leg! Munsey is a goner, but he has played a perfect hand. Second wicket for Rashid, gives England an opening

tossed up on the stumps, MacLeod goes back and whips through the leg side, they'll come back for the second - that's his hundred, from just 70 balls, a seventh in ODIs for MacLeod and the first by a Scotland batsman against England! Off comes the helmet, he takes the applause for a brilliant innings
drops back and swats a single to keep the strike
fired wide of the stumps and he can't get anything on it
drops back, swiped over backward point, that's going to race away for four
full, now this is carted over the leg side, MacLeod manoeuvering the field as the swings it for four more
length outside off, maybe a slower ball and he misses with a reverse-swat
full and aiming for the tramlines, swing and a miss
another dot ball for Willey, good comeback as again he slips one through in the channel
pushed through on the stumps, Budge gets off the mark first ball with a nurdle to leg
dragged down and this is fodder, even hitting against the spin, hammered between deep midwicket and long-on for four
tossed up and crunched flat on the pull for one to deep square
pushed through outside off, steered square for one
floated up full, MacLeod tries to get under the slog-sweep but only sends it on the bounce to deep backward square
slips in the Bosie and Budge hangs back, pokes through square leg for one
full and wide of the stumps, Budge whacks it through point
pitched up, aiming for the timbers this time and MacLeod shovels it wide of long-on for a couple
pitched up outside off, MacLeod goes for the rolling-AB-scoop over deep backward square... but ends up being nutmegged by the ball
very full, can't get under it, slugged to deep cover for one
wide full toss, Budge plinks it for one
very full again, MacLeod rolls out the reverse-slap and sends it to short third man... so a boundary-free over: a rare wee beastie today
hits the pitch hard, good pace and it flies through over the stumps as MacLeod goes back and swings hard but fails to connect
fired in full on middle and leg, dug out down the ground for one
shortish and coming in on the angle, Budge runs one down to third man
short ball, taking the pace off... and then putting the pace back on at a rate of knots, into the camera gantry over deep midwicket, right out of the screws!
MacLeod backs away and is then left on his knees as Wood goes full outside off, swing and a miss
full length, drilled through the off side to the sweeper - this is now Scotland's highest ODI score
short of a length, the offcutter but MacLeod is sat on the back foot and he clubs four more out to deep midwicket
goes full outside off, MacLeod dances across and scoops over the ring, that's four more to fine leg - Scotland raise 350 for the first time in ODIs!
moves outside off stump again, banged in short and pulled down off the bottom edge for one
short ball, that's tonked over midwicket for four more! Budge giving it a nudge now
fired in full outside off, swatted through the covers
short again, pulled again, this goes racing away to the leg-side boundary again... Plunkett not bowling to his field and the runs continue to bleed
timber! Off stump out of the ground... That's a good death-overs delivery, full and quick and sending Budge back as he misses with a big old yahoo
pitched up but he's not landed the yorker and Leask blooters it straight back down the ground, six from his first ball!
full and whipped through mid-on, they come haring back for two
full and wide and stabbed through the covers for a single
full toss sprayed down the leg side, looks like being a wide... but it flicked MacLeod's pad on its way through to Billings, and they ran anyway
pitched up, Leask can't get under it, just one through the covers... but that is still a fantastic effort from Scotland

inn2.comm: short of a length outside off, Roy doesn't quite get his timing as he drives to mid-off from the back foot
just short! Not far from carrying to backward point as Roy square drives a short delivery doesn't really keep it down
pushed down the leg side, there's half an appeal for a catch. No wide given so must have clipped the pad

short of a length, nudged just in front of square and they are quick between the wickets. The third umpire just checks for the run out as it's a direct hit. Roy did just place his bat in, but he's fine
good length, straight, defended
back of a length, at the batsman, played back to the bowler
full at the pads, clipped behind square and there's good work around the boundary by Dylan Budge
short of a length, angled into the pads, nicely timed off his pads through square and there's more work for Budge
short outside off, delivers from quite wide of the crease, Roy gets onto his toes and drills it off the back foot to cover
angled into the body and that's a good piece of timing and is works it through midwicket
full outside off, he comes forward and drives to mid-off
short and hammered through square leg, sweet connection as he swivels on a strong pull shot
excellent timing and placement through the off side, just short of a length, punched off the back foot through the covers and it runs away from mid-off
back of a length, quite tight to off stump, back cut wide of the lone slip to third man
well bowled, touch of extra bounce from back of a length, takes the splice of Roy's bat
back of a length, 80mph, just outside off, pushed into the covers
gets onto his toes and places a sweet back-foot drive but can't beat cover
full at off stump, flicked into the on side but mid-on is able to get across to his right
short of a length outside off, Bairstow forcing off the back foot and gets a thickish outside edge to third man
full outside off and slotted through the covers with a strong drive off the front foot
this is cracked off the back foot back towards the bowler
back of a length outside off, angled to third man with an open face
full and straight, a hint of movement into the batsman, driven to mid-on
power! Short and wide outside off, Bairstow doesn't miss out, unleashes a fierce square cut which reaches the rope before any blinks
full, angled into the pads, flicked to deep square leg
another one through the off side, full at the stumps, Bairstow is forward and plays a punchy-drive wide of mid-off
drags the length back, at the stumps, pushed to mid-on
this is lovely placement, more width outside off, Bairstow cuts it just behind point and third man can't get across
gets forward and drives on the up into the covers where Munsey misfields
full at the pads, clipped off the toes to deep square leg. Lively start from England
round the wicket, starts by dropping one short outside off, Roy rocks back and cuts into backward point where it slips through the fielder's grasp
full at the stumps, defended to cover
cut into point
played off the back foot into the covers
that's a lovely shot, dances down the pitch and opens up the off side then drives inside out over extra cover
pushed through quicker and flatter, driven to mid-off
very full outside off, driven from the toe end to mid-off
clipped towards mid-on
punched with a straight bat wide of a diving short midwicket and down to long-on
gets forward into a full delivery outside off and drives to mid-off who is inside the circle
dragged down a touch short but Roy misses out as he mistimes his pull to midwicket
touch more air this time, full and straight, worked to deep midwicket. Steady start from Leask
full at the stumps, he plays with a slightly open face but can't find a gap at cover
clipped down the ground to long-on
short outside off, crunched through the off side but it was in the air for a while just wide of a diving Coetzer
and this time he clears long-off with a lovely clean swing of the arms, a lofted drive down the ground
fuller at the stumps, dragged into the leg side down to long-on
driven back to the bowler
gets down on his back knee and sweeps high over square leg, drops just short of being a six
and now he skips down the pitch, lovely footwork, and clips this effortlessly over deep midwicket
and now it's straight down the ground! A 27-ball fifty for him as he drills a full delivery over the sight screen
pushes a flatter delivery back to the bowler
short, dragged down the leg side, Bairstow misses his pull and it rebounds off the keeper's pads wide of short fine leg
goes downtown again! Full, a hint of width outside off, he stands in the crease and just plays a lofted drive over long-off
shorter, flatter, outside off, he plays back and picks out the man at point with a square drive
back of a length outside off, driven from the back foot to mid-off
full and straight, driven to mid-off from the front foot
a short-arm jab over midwicket for six! Just short of a length, Bairstow muscles it over the leg side
what a short! That's a skimming drive in the air over cover, drives on the up when offered just a hint of width and England's hundred is up in the 10th over
short, width outside off, slashes away over backward point down to the vacant third man
back of a length outside off, gives himself a hint of room to the leg side then plays this to backward point
over the wicket, short of a length outside off, driven to long-off...they briefly thought of the second
full and straight, pushed down the ground to long-on
full outside off, he leans forward and drives down the ground
poor ball, full outside leg stump, Bairstow sweeps the medium pacer and though short fine-leg gets a hand on it he can't cut it off
on the pads, but this time Bairstow's flick is intercepted by midwicket
what a shot! Power and elegance from Bairstow as he drives a full delivery through the covers with barely any effort
now it's Roy's turn to flay through the off side as he gets onto the front foot, goes wide of the cover sweeper
beats the edge! I repeat, beats the edge...not seen many of them today. Back of a length, Roy aiming to drive through the coevrs
full outside off, a bottom-handed flick straight down the ground
short, and pulled miles over deep midwicket into the footcourt! A poor ball, medium pace and dragged down, Bairstow doesn't miss out
goes full at the stumps, firmly clipped to long-on
good work at backward point as he springs to his right to cut off Roy's square drive
big appeal for lbw as Bairstow goes for the sweep! Hit his back leg but was there an edge? Don't think so, maybe heading down the leg side
another sweep that doesn't go right, gets a bottom edge into his back leg
angled into the pads from round the wicket, worked to deep square leg
breakthrough! Spin does the trick. Roy pushes a length ball back for a simple return catch. May have just held in the surface. Good bowling, good captaincy
plays back and pushes out to deep cover
full and straight, pushed back to the bowler...so he won't be breaking Buttler's record
back of a length, straight, defended to mid-on
touch fuller, he gets forward and times his drive nicely but Evans does well to get down in his follow through
good length, defended to mid-off
tight to off stump, good length, defended to the off side...good stuff from Evans
beats the edge! Hales looking to force off the back foot through the covers
back of a length at off stump, defended to cover...a maiden, super effort
flicked off the stumps to midwicket
gets down early and plays a very neat paddle sweep fine of short fine leg
slides on towards off stump, he gives himself a touch of room then cuts to cover
fuller, at the stumps, driven to cover

another huge appeal for lbw as Bairstow misses a sweep...takes the back leg and another not out. Delivered from wide on the crease, so the angle not in his favour. They decline the review. Was missing leg stump
full, angled into leg stump, heaved through the leg side, is it flicked back by the rope, or is it his hundred? Sole the fielder and looks like he's done very well.
full and straight, nudged into the leg side
full and straight, flicked to long-on to take him to 99
back of a length outside off, pushed to deep cover
gets in a yorker at off stump, jabbed to the covers and Hales sends him back
flicks a full ball wide of midwicket and there's his hundred off 54 balls
angled into the pads, clipped behind square to the man in the deep
starts with a short ball which is hooked over long leg, a hint of top edge from Hales but comfortably over the rope
full, angled in at the toes, and that's a sweet piece of timing through midwicket
pulls the length back, on middle, defended to the bowler
short of a length outside off, driven to deep point from the back foot
super work at cover! Bairstow crunched that drive off the front foot, Coetzer leading from the front by hurling himself in the way
that's high, very, very high, straight down the ground...a length ball is sent into the crowd over long-on
over the wicket, dobbed on a length and whipped away behind square with a bottom-handed flick, Bairstow hares back for two
full outside off, he's forward to flay this one to the covers sweeper
pace off, 68mph outside off, Hales chops down and it runs away behind square, they jog through
driven on the up from the crease, single through the covers again
on a length, squired down the ground to long-off

slogged towards long-off... the Bairstow express has gone off the tracks! Munsey holds a steepler, running around the rope before steadying himself to complete the dismissal. Berrington's medium-pace does the trick, Scotland needed that
touch short and driven into the off side
goes wide on the crease, short of a length and Hales gets across to block
back of a length, Hales waits and turns a single off his hip
touch short, 81mph and Root caresses it off the back foot, gliding behind point and in front of third man to get off the mark with a four first ball
better length, 83mph and defended on off stump
short, Root rolls his wrists on a pull to deep square leg
fullish, dinked through the covers on the front foot
comes across and punches to cover
full, angling in and flicked through the leg side
length outside off, Root dabs one down to third man
on the toes, worked into a gap on the leg side
length outside off, Root drops back and glides another single
defended into the on side
drops short, 82mph and it sits up to be spanked, Hales whirls his arms up through a powerful roundhouse for four to deep midwicket
full, tapped towards mid-off coming forwards
good length on off, 84mph but Hales does well to cushion it towards mid-off, just a tip and run and he's home despite the underarm direct hit
on the stumps, worked across the line for one
Root shuffles across and tucks to the leg side
wicket-to-wicket stuff with the keeper up, nudged away

down the leg side, Cross takes it smartly and then whips off the bails as Root overbalances... was his foot grounded? I think Cross broke the bails before he fell forward, but they'll check this with the TV umpire. The keeper actually went for a second crack, which would require him to take a stump out; but yes, replays show his foot was down
pitched up and punched wide of mid-on
on the stumps, whipped through backward square
tight stuff, punched back to the on side
slightly short and Hales draws himself up in the crease to lash four more through the covers. Hard to keep any pressure on for the fielding side here
tossed up and tapped away
drifting a touch too straight now, Root gets down and paddles the ball away for four
prodded into a gap
angled in with the arm, Hales taps back to the bowler
tossed up and pushed into the covers
pushed through, Hales punches along the ground and Watt dives across to his right to field
pitched up in the channel, Root strokes a drive to point
full on the toes, Root waits for it and flicks one to deep square leg
good-length ball, Hales comes across and pings a drive along the carpet to mid-off
full and swinging a touch but that's drifted leg side, Hales misses with a flick
length, 77mph on off stump, tapped in front of extra cover
slightly short of as length, Hales drives square at the top of the bounce and they hustle back for two
overptiched, that's in the slot and Hales brutalises it back down the ground over long-off! Mind the windows
lobbed up from round the wicket, Root tickles a single through mid-off
angled in and defended on the stumps
Watt tosses the all up on middle and leg, Hales blocks to midwicket

angled in with a low arm, Hales sweeps and is hit in front, Watt likes it... but Erasmus turns down the appeal, and Scotland take too long in asking for a review! Coetzer wanted to go to the DRS but Erasmus tells him time has run out
tossed up and swatted away for on behind square
flat on the stumps and nudged to leg
angled in with the arm, Hales turns to the leg side
gets into line and blocks on off
touch short, Hales stays back and throws the hands through a drive, just one to the cover sweeper
Root turns this into a gap for one
on the stumps, prodded back to the bowler
back of a length, Hales moves across and drills a back-foot punch to long-on
lobbed on the stumps and worked to the on side
tossed up full, Root defends
cleverly done by Root, comes across and paddles the ball fine, no one there and he'll get four
flatter, jabbed into the off side
floated up, that's in the arc for Root's slog-sweep and he nails it, hard and flat into the crowd at deep midwicket!

dragged down, Root swivels to pulls, sends it off the bottom edge to short fine leg... but what's this, Hales has called for the run and Root is struggling desperately to get to the other end! Leask collects the throw and breaks the stumps and Root looks like he knows he's gone, here! Yes, out by a yard, England lose another in rather needless circumstances
overpitched, angled across and Morgan steps on to the front foot and eases it through the covers for a first-ball four
on the stumps, Morgan closes the face and tucks a couple through midwicket
slower ball, slightly leg side and Morgan nudges one more off his pads
good length on off stump, Hales taps it away
touch short, punched down the ground from the crease
pitched up, driven into the ground and Sharif dives to his left to field in his follow through
tossed up and worked away for a single
pushed through from round the wicket, no turn and Morgan punches through cover
back over the wicket, lobbed up and met coming forwards
flat on the stumps, Hales is down to sweep powerfully through backward square - that's fifty up for Hales, puttering along at just under a run-a-ball
touch short, Morgan spots it - launched high into the crowd at deep midwicket! That came sweetly off the middle
pushed through flat and Morgan strokes one coming across
round the wicket, angled in on the stumps, clipped into a gap at square leg for a couple
length ball, 67mph outside off, driven down the ground
over the wicket, Hales leans on a forward defensive
full on off stump, clouted back down the ground and Berrington gets a hand on it in his follow through but can't prevent one
fullish, driven down the ground
pitched up, tight lines and Hales taps it away
angled across from over the wicket, Morgan punches through cover
full, Hales flays it up and over cover point for one
comes across and pokes into the off side
length, 83mph, tapped down towards midwicket
full toss, Morgan wallops it to extra cover

looped off the hip, into the leg side, Coetzer takes an excellent running catch! Well, there's a wicket, just what Scotland needed! Evans does it, got this to skip up from back of a length and Morgan spliced it in front of midwicket - a sharp chance, but well taken with both hands above his head

another one, Hales slaps straight to point! Two in two balls for Scotland and this game has come alive again! Hales slumps on his bat, that was basically a wide long hop, but he has picked out Evans, who takes the catch to follow up his breakthrough with the ball
round the wicket, length ball outside off, Moeen pushes and is beaten
on the pads, worked away through midwicket to get off the mark
full outside off, Billings leans into a drive and sends it along the ground to mid-off
back of a length, 74mph outside off stump, cut towards point from the crease
full and angling in, Billings works it down the ground through mid-on
slung down the leg side, that's a freebie
full, 81mph and punched back past the bowler
dangles the carrot outside off, good length and Moeen wafts a drive, beaten
gets across and punches a single this time
full and straight, Billings pings a drive to mid-on
dropped into the off side, Billings scampers through safely for one, despite a direct hit at the bowler's end
short and tucking him up around the ribs, Moeen jabs it down
full, taking the pace off, punched through the covers
angled across, Moeen strokes one through the covers
full and Billings picks out extra cover
on the stumps, tucked through midwicket for a single
no width on offer, Moeen is happy to work a single to leg
pitched up on off stump, Billings prods one more back through mid-off
full and straight, clipped to long-on
full outside off, strides forward and drives to deep cover
low full and it gets driven straight down the ground...a rare poor ball in the last period from Scotland
clipped off the toes out to deep midwicket
full at middle, clipped to midwicket and it's a good save
length ball, straight, defended to mid-on
low full toss, straight to short midwicket! So Billings can't take his chance, and Scotland favourites now. he can't believe it, ball was there for hitting, but he just picked out the man
round the wicket, full outside off, driven to long-off
worked off the stumps to midwicket
takes this off the pads behind square but can't beat short fine leg
on the pads again and this time he flicks it with plenty of bottom hand over deep midwicket
pushed back to the bowler
very graceful from Willey, gets forward and calmly drives a length delivery wide of mid-off
banged in short and Willey pulls through square leg, good work on the rope by Budge
and another! Scotland surging. Another short ball, this time slightly further outside off, Willey gets a top edge as he pulls
that's a beauty! Beats Plunkett's outside edge which holds its line just outside off stump
back of a length, played with an open face to backward point
low full toss, driven towards mid-off
gets forward to a length ball and plays to cover
chipped in the air, through the vacant mid-on area down the ground
that's high and handsome over extra cover - caught in the crowd - as Moeen plays a graceful lofted drive
full outside off, driven to long-off
driven into the off side
edged, just wide of the keeper, flashing at a full delivery outside off, takes a thick edge and just evades the outstretched right glove
short of a length outside off, played off the back foot to point
angled into the pads, pushed to midwicket
another short one, outside off, and no timing from Plunkett as he flat-bats it back to the bowler
full and straight, driven to mid-off
angled into the pads, worked through midwicket and they are able to get back for the second
low full toss which is driven to long-off
back of a length outside off, punched at the top of the bounce to deep cover
short of a length at middle and off, played back to the bowler
big full toss, wide outside off, sliced behind square between backward point and short third man
short ball, a slower delivery, pulled in front of square
goes for the yorker, dug out to the leg side
back of a length outside off, opens the face and runs it to third man
full and straight, driven down the ground
full, speared down the leg side, good work by the keeper to prevent further extras
drives a back-of-a-length ball to backward point
clips this off the toes straight to short fine leg, a foot either side and that was a boundary
short outside off, that's put away well by Plunkett as he goes up and over backward point
short of a length outside off, clubbed down to long-on
uses his feet and then gets this off the leading edge to the on side
full and straight, driven to deep cover
good delivery, fires in a yorker, jabbed to the off side
pushes a length ball back to the bowler
fired in full at leg stump, Plunkett aims to turn this quite square through the leg side but gets it down to long-on
low full toss outside off, only costs a single as Moeen drives to deep cover
worked off the pads to deep square leg
gets a thick inside edge as he drives at a length ball
full outside off, the bottom hand comes into play as he drags this out to deep midwicket
full on leg stump, clipped out to deep midwicket
dropped in short and pulled, a skimming shot, over deep square leg. He struck that very sweetly
gets back on a good length at off stump, defended
that's another fantastic shot from Moeen, full outside off, drives inside out over cover, wide of long-off
low full toss, clipped to long-on
full at leg stump, worked to midwicket
on off stump this time, driven to cover for another dot ball
finds a gap this time as he pushes it straight down the ground
down the pitch, makes it into a full toss but then mistimes it down the ground
round the wicket, back of a length, and that's just heaved dismissively over midwicket
and now he goes over the top with grace and elegance, a length ball outside off, drives through the line and it's miles back into the crowd
flicks a length delivery from outside off down to long-on
and now it's Plunkett's turn to go down the ground, stays in his crease and drives through the line...couldn't send it much straighter. Lovely shot

huge appeal for a catch down the leg side! Not out. Must have been pad because there's no wide call. Did Plunkett over-balance out of his crease? Yes, he did, he was well out of his ground. Cross was busy appealing
tucked off the pads behind square on the leg side
very full outside off, skewed into the leg side as he drives...bowled from well behind the crease
full and straight, eased down to long-off
he's found long-on! There's a twist in this game yet...he tries to clean long-on, but doesn't find the middle. He also had to fetch it from outside off. Munsey settles under it
angled in from round the wicket, on middle and leg, defended
very full outside off, pushed to cover
pushes a length ball into the covers
full outside off, driven to deep cover
low full toss outside off, drives and gets it down the ground to long-on without much timing
a slower ball, superbly bowled, does Rashid completely as it beats the top edge
offers some width outside off, Rashid drives square but the sweeper keeps it to a single
argh! Gets the line wrong, on the pads, Plunkett flicks it fine of short fine leg
well bowled, some late inswing on that yorker, pushed down the ground to long-off. Scotland have found some reverse late on
back of a length, swings in quite significantly, pushed into the off side
short outside off, Rashid goes over cover, didn't find the middle and plops in front of the sweeper
full and straight, met with a straight bat as he drives down the ground to long-off
short of a length, shapes in at off stump, dropped to the off side and that's good running
a strangled appeal for lbw as this swings in late and takes the pad, Plunkett playing to the leg side, but it's heading well down the leg side

desperation all round! Plunkett swings at a yorker, squeezes it into the leg side, sets off for a scampered run, Sole bounds across from his follow through, dives, collects and almost hits at the non-striker's end. Would have been tight

Rashid is gone here! What drama! Coming back for the second. Plunkett swung this down the ground, just wide of long-on, and they chanced the second. Strong throw from the deep by Leask and a good gather at the stumps
full and straight, firmly down the ground to long-off...England can't take any risks now
low full toss on the pads, could have been costly but it's just clipped to deep square
full ball, heaved in the air through midwicket, again wide of long-on but they won't be taking on Leask's arm this time
SCOTLAND HAVE DONE IT A brilliant yorker traps Wood in front and the ground erupts. What a delivery, late inswing, takes Wood on the boot. Incredible scenes.
